Package io.github.struppigel.parser

This is the main package for the Portable Executable format parser.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Characteristic
    Represents characteristic flags used by the PE format.
    HeaderKey
    Represents a key for a StandardField.
    PEModule
    Represents a structure in the PE file.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ByteArrayUtil
    Utilities to convert from and to byte arrays.
    FlagUtil
    Utility methods for flag-related operations.
    Header<T extends HeaderKey>
    Represents a header of the pe file or a header of a section.
    IOUtil
    Utilities for file IO needed to read maps and arrays from the text files in the data subdirectory of PortEx.
    IOUtil.SpecificationFormat
    Describes the format/indices of the specification file.
    Location
    Abstract location.
    Location$  
    Mapping
    Maps all addresses of a virtual range to all addresses of the physical range.
    Mapping$  
    MemoryMappedPE
    Represents the PE file content as it is mapped to memory.
    MemoryMappedPE$
    Responsible for creating the memory mappings
    PEData
    Container that collects and holds the main information of a PE file.
    PELoader
    Loads PEData of a file.
    PESignature
    Reads the offset of the PE signature and the signature itself.
    PhysicalLocation
    Location in a file on disk.
    PhysRange
    Represents a range of physical addresses
    Range
    Simply a range with start and end.
    RichHeader
    Reads the Rich Header if it exists
    RichHeader$  
    ScalaIOUtil
    Utilities for Scala specific IO and small conversions related to IO.
    ScalaIOUtil$
    Utilities for Scala specific IO and small conversions related to IO.
    StandardField
    A data class for a typical entry of PE Headers.
    VirtRange
    Represents a range of in-memory addresses
    VirtualLocation
    Location in virtual space.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    FileFormatException
    Is thrown if a specification file doesn't have the expected formatting, for example wrong delimiters.

Package io.github.struppigel.parser Description

This is the main package for the Portable Executable format parser.

This is the heart of PortEx.
